<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="TPa7">
<l>kīcu kīceṉṟu eṅkum āṉaic cāttāṉ kalantu</l>
<l>pēciṉa pēccaravam kēṭṭilaiyō pēyp peṇṇē</l>
<l>kācum piṟappum kalakalappak kai pērttu</l>
<l>vāca naṟum kuḻal āycciyar mattiṉāl</l>
<l>ōcai paṭutta tayiraravam kēṭṭilaiyō</l>
<l>nāyakap peṇ piḷḷāy nārāyaṇaṉ mūrtti</l>
<l>kēcavaṉaip pāṭavum nī kēṭṭē kiṭattiyō</l>
<l>tēcamuṭaiyāy tiṟavēlōr empāvāy</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>O foolish girl! Have you not heard</l>
<l rend="indent">chirpings everywhere,</l>
<l rend="indent">the sound of the talks uttered by the meeting king crows?</l>
<l>Have you not heard the sound of curd[-making]</l>
<l rend="indent">as the cowherdesses, with [their] hair fragrant with aromatic products,</l>
<l rend="indent">move their arms, making noise with the churning staff</l>
<l rend="indent">so that the kācu- and the piṟappu- necklaces tinkle?</l>
<l>O chief among girls! Are you [still] lying down,</l>
<l>even after hearing [our] singing about Nārāyaṇa, Keśava, [our] Lord?</l>
<l>Open [the door], O lustrous [girl]!</l>
<l>O our maidens, accept [and] consider [this] attentively!</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
